<figure id="attachment_71902" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-71902" style="width: 450px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2025-10-09-tight-quarters-1.jpg" alt="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Bishop_Rock_Lighthouse_SV8006.jpg" width="450" height="599" class="size-full wp-image-71902" srcset="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2025-10-09-tight-quarters-1.jpg 450w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2025-10-09-tight-quarters-1-300x399.jpg 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-71902" class="wp-caption-text">Image: <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Bishop_Rock_Lighthouse_SV8006.jpg">Wikimedia Commons</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>The world&#8217;s smallest island with a building on it is the Bishop Rock, a skerry off the coast of Cornwall. The islet is 46 by 16 meters, and the tower&#8217;s base is 10 meters across. Before the installation of a helipad in 1976, visitors would rappel from the tower&#8217;s base to waiting boats.</p>
<figure id="attachment_71903" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-71903" style="width: 960px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2025-10-09-tight-quarters-2.jpg" alt="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Thousand_Islands_single_house.jpg" width="960" height="632" class="size-full wp-image-71903" srcset="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2025-10-09-tight-quarters-2.jpg 960w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2025-10-09-tight-quarters-2-600x395.jpg 600w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2025-10-09-tight-quarters-2-300x198.jpg 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-71903" class="wp-caption-text">Image: <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Thousand_Islands_single_house.jpg">Wikimedia Commons</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>Among the Thousand Islands at the head of the Saint Lawrence River is the smallest inhabited island in the world, known as &#8220;Just Room Enough.&#8221; It accommodates a single house.</p>
<figure id="attachment_71904" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-71904" style="width: 960px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2025-10-09-tight-quarters-3.jpg" alt="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Smallest_House_in_Great_Britain,_Conwy_(8035).jpg" width="960" height="638" class="size-full wp-image-71904" srcset="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2025-10-09-tight-quarters-3.jpg 960w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2025-10-09-tight-quarters-3-600x399.jpg 600w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2025-10-09-tight-quarters-3-300x199.jpg 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-71904" class="wp-caption-text">Image: <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Smallest_House_in_Great_Britain,_Conwy_(8035).jpg">Wikimedia Commons</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>The &#8220;Smallest House in Great Britain&#8221; stands on the quay in Conwy, Wales. Built in the 16th century, it has a floor area of 3.05 by 1.8 meters.</p>
<figure id="attachment_71905" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-71905" style="width: 500px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2025-10-09-tight-quarters-4.jpg" alt="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Drumheller,_AB,_Canada_-_panoramio.jpg" width="500" height="737" class="size-full wp-image-71905" srcset="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2025-10-09-tight-quarters-4.jpg 500w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2025-10-09-tight-quarters-4-300x442.jpg 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-71905" class="wp-caption-text">Image: <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Drumheller,_AB,_Canada_-_panoramio.jpg">Wikimedia Commons</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>Built in 1958, the Little Church in Drumheller, Alberta, is <a href="https://www.drumhellerchamber.com/your-chamber/the-little-church">available for ceremonies</a>. It seats six.</p>
